# Cursor Rules for KUNI_2thecore_frontend

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 15 React TypeScript project for a vehicle management system (차량 관제 시스템).

## Code Style Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Use functional components with React hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow Next.js 15 App Router conventions
- Use shadcn/ui components when available
- Prefer single quotes
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for components

## File Structure
- Components: `src/components/`
- Pages: `src/app/`
- Hooks: `src/hooks/`
- Store: `src/store/`
- Types: `src/types/`
- Utils: `src/utils.ts`

## Dependencies
- zustand for state management
- react-hook-form for forms
- zod for validation
- lucide-react for icons
- radix-ui for UI components

## Code Generation Rules
- Always include proper TypeScript types
- Use proper error handling
- Include accessibility attributes
- Follow React best practices
- Use proper imports and exports
- Include JSDoc comments for complex functions

## Performance Considerations
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Optimize re-renders with useMemo and useCallback
- Use proper key props for lists
- Lazy load components when appropriate

## Testing
- Prefer unit tests for utilities
- Use React Testing Library for component tests
- Mock external dependencies

## Project-Specific Conventions
- Use Korean comments for business logic
- Follow the existing component naming patterns
- Maintain the current file organization structure
- Use the existing state management patterns with zustand 